channel.title: [Delta] Removing gates?
channel.description:
I've been at this for a while.
The Camelot gates won't remove from DeletethatObject.
How would you be able to remove the gates?

item.title: [Delta] Removing gates?
item.dc:creator: @Jddogg9 Jddogg9
item.description:
@Jddogg9 wrote:

DivineSouls:

Doors aren’t like regular objects, they are placed in between tiles. deleteThatObject method is really just deleting anything that is on a tile. I personally am not aware of ways to delete gates and such, there probably is, if you have a method that can delve into the cache. I’m assuming you want to delete the gates because they don’t open? You can make the gates open with a if statement. Tell me if you want that.

There has to be a way to “remove” the object. I saw a boolean that stated it would replace the object.

ReplaceThatObject2 or something on the lines of that.

Read full topic
